1 0 0 1 48.00 442.00 Tm (2. High-Level Request Flow) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 413.00 Tm (Example: citizen reports an issue.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 392.00 Tm (1. User opens React app at http://localhost:5173.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 377.00 Tm (2. App.jsx routes user to /auth, /citizen, /officer, or /admin.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 362.00 Tm (3. User logs in through AuthPage.jsx.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 347.00 Tm (4. Frontend sends request through client/src/api/axios.js to backend API at) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 333.00 Tm (http://localhost:5000.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 318.00 Tm (5. Backend route receives request, for example POST /api/auth/login/citizen.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 303.00 Tm (6. Controller validates user from MongoDB, checks password using bcrypt, creates JWT, and) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 289.00 Tm (returns user data.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 274.00 Tm (7. Frontend stores token, role, and user in sessionStorage.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 259.00 Tm (8. Protected dashboard pages attach token to API calls using Axios interceptor.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 244.00 Tm (9. Backend protect middleware verifies token and loads req.user.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 229.00 Tm (10. Role guards such as citizenOnly, officerOnly, and adminOnly allow or block access.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 214.00 Tm (11. Controller performs database operation using Mongoose models.) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 62.00 199.00 Tm (12. Response returns JSON to React, and React updates UI state.) Tj
/F2 15 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 179.00 Tm (3. Frontend Code Flow) Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 48.00 150.00 Tm (Entry Files) Tj
